title: Led Zeppelin - 1973.05.14 New Orleans, Louisiana
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1973.05.14 New Orleans, Louisiana   

Led Zeppelin
Municipal Auditorium
New Orleans, LA
May 14th 1973
Audience patched with soundboard

Audience Source: 
Incomplete very good to excellent audience recording.
Details: 
This is a truly a wonderful find. It is very dynamic 
and atmospheric and is thus generally more enjoyable 
than the soundboard

Soundboard Source: 
Incomplete excellent soundboard recording.
Details: 
The recording is a very good balanced professional 
board tape that favors bass and drums.

Tracklist:

CD 1
1. Rock And Roll
2. Celebration Day
3. Black Dog
4. Over The Hills And Far Away
5. Misty Mountain Hop  
6. Since I've Been Loving You	
7. No Quarter
8. The Song Remains the Same
9. The Rain Song (cut)

CD 2 
1. Dazed And Confused
2. Stairway To Heaven
3. Moby Dick (cut)

CD 3
1. Heartbreaker
2. Whole Lotta Love (medley)
3. Communication Breakdown

Comments: 
If the previous show was nirvana, this one is beyond that. An excellent
show with rowdy audience that caused the reaction from the side of the 
authorities. "We've got to get these house lights down. It's pretty 
pointless us bringing our own lights, if we've got these things going 
on. Mr Cole, can you take your dress off and get these lights turned 
down please?" asked Plant in rather humorously mood. His voice is 
cracking and breaking all over the place, but the band is playing 
exceptionally well, and from Dazed And Confused on, this show reaches 
its peak. Dazed has a unique, very dark and thrilling bow solo and 
Heartbreaker, Whole Lotta Love and the encore are gutsy and raw and 
Robert has recovered. John Bonham was introduced as the Drag Queen of 
New Orleans
